Preheat the #oven{} to 200°C. Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a large #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. Pop the @chicken breast{260%g}(diced) into a #mixing bowl{} and add half the @North Indian style spice mix{1} and a glug of @oil{}. Grate in half the @lime{1} zest and mix well, making sure that your chicken is well coated. Halve and peel the @red onion{1/2}, then cut each half into quarters. Separate the layers of the red onion.

> The remaining lime juice will be used for the salad and satay sauce.

When the water is boiling, add the @star anise{1} and @basmati rice{150%g} to the pan. Lower the heat to medium and pop a lid on the pan. Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat and set aside (still covered) for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

> TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Meanwhile, thread one piece of chicken onto a @bamboo skewers{} and follow it with a piece of red onion. Repeat this process until all of your chicken and red onion is used. You want two skewers per person.

Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat and add a glug of @oil{}. When the oil is hot, cook the chicken skewers for ~{2-3%minutes} on each side.

> TIP: You want them to be golden brown so do this in batches if necessary.

Transfer the kebabs to a #baking tray{} and pop in your oven for ~{12-15%minutes}.

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken cooks, trim the @cucumber{1/2} then quarter lengthways, and chop widthways into small pieces. Pop the chopped cucumber into another mixing bowl. Roughly chop the @coriander{1/2%bunch} (stalks and all) and add to the bowl.

> TIP: If you're a coriander fan, add the whole bunch!

Add half the lime juice and the @soy sauce{12.5%ml} and mix well. Taste and add a little @?sugar{} if it needs sweetening.

== Satay Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{} mix the remaining curry powder with the @peanut butter{1%tbsp}. Stir in the remaining lime juice and the @water{200%ml} for the sauce.

> TIP: The consistency of the satay sauce should be similar to double cream, so add another splash of water if necessary.

Season with a @salt{pinch}.

== To Serve ==

Once the rice has finished cooking, remove the star anise and fluff up the rice with a #fork{}. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

To serve, spoon a generous amount of rice in the centre of a #plate{} and top with the cucumber salad. Place the chicken satay kebabs on top and finish with a drizzle of the satay sauce. Enjoy!